# django_dynamic_path

A replacement for django's path(), allowing for truly dynamic urls. Rather than specifying a regular expression to define a url, you specify a "resolver function". This function will be given the path, and can perform database lookups, filesystem lookups, etc. before deciding whether or not to handle the request.



